{"tid":1392511,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"本土派英裔香港人教你如何文宣","createTime":"2019-07-31T18:36:01.000Z","updateTime":"2019-08-14T13:37:06.000Z","uid":215715,"like":149,"dislike":1,"uniUserReply":42,"replies":[{"pid":"51e21ecb1cf3f2c5bf80add5badade25607f66bf","tid":1392511,"uid":215715,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-07-31T18:36:01.000Z","msg":"Richard Scotford: If Hong Kongers are to fully embrace protest culture then they need to shed the mindset that being arrested is a thing of shame. <br />\n<br />\n要令香港人如果要完全擁抱示威文化既話，我地要令放棄被補即恥辱既諗法。<br />\n<br />\nThose arrested need to be elevated to the level of political martyrs.<br />\n不幸被補既義士應該要提升到一個政治烈士既地位。<br />\n<br />\nTheir stories and images need to be all across the city. On every wall, every bridge. <br />\n將佢地既事跡宣揚開去，遍佈整個香港，所有牆，所有橋上面。<br />\n<br />\nThis is already happening with Ed Leung, which is totally awesome, but a revolution can NOT happen if those who are about to pay heaviest prices are not celebrated for their sacrifices.<br />\n<br />\n天琦係一個絕佳既例子，但革命係唔會出現，如果付上嚴重代價既人冇得到欣賞。<br />\n<br />\n-<br />\n <a href=\"https://www.wsj.com/articles/a-teenager-pilot-and-teacher-accused-hong-kong-rioters-reflect-protests-diversity-11564572356\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fa-teenager-pilot-and-teacher-accused-hong-kong-rioters-reflect-protests-diversity-11564572356&d=puaUx2dgpXXsrsLU9noyGKooFDKVeMyzaQj0gYzwHSI%3D&h=acaeb7ae\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.wsj.com/articles/a-teenager-pilot-and-teacher-accused-hong-kong-rioters-reflect-protests-diversity-11564572356</a>"},{"pid":"1fffa97ba8d9809bcc3c11ee6b5c345873c612e2","tid":1392511,"uid":144522,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-07-31T18:37:55.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"988b68352d3e121c6830010013320c117baf3f6b","tid":1392511,"uid":167177,"like":21,"dislike":0,"score":21,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":